<P><PB N="179" REF="106">
The next day in the Morning being &s;ent for to the Court, I found the <HI>Nazar,</HI> the Grand Trea&s;urer, and &s;everal other great&punc; Officers expecting me in the Trea|&s;ury, where the Money lay ready in &s;eal'd Bags. My Sum amounted to three thou&s;and four hundred and &s;ixty <HI>Tomans,</HI> of which the Trea&s;urer would have abated me a hundred and &s;ixty for Fees. After a long conte&s;t, I gave him half, and carry'd away my Money; having fir&s;t weigh'd two Bags <HI>Toman</HI> by <HI>Toman,</HI> and then weigh'd the re&s;t of the Bags, Bag by Bag.</P>
